REST = multiple endpoints, each returns a fixed structure.
GraphQL = one endpoint, you ask for exactly what you need.

```
# REST — multiple requests for related data
GET /api/user/1
GET /api/user/1/posts
GET /api/user/1/followers

# GraphQL — one request, you specify the shape
POST /graphql
{
  user(id: 1) {
    name
    posts { title }
    followers { name }
  }
}
```

REST is simpler and well-understood. GraphQL is more flexible — you never over-fetch or under-fetch data. most apps do fine with REST. GraphQL shines when you have complex, nested data and mobile apps that need to minimize requests.

